<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/289: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-05T17:00:00-04:00">June
                                        5, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>56. Your 185, June 1, 5 p.m. The notification sent to the Italian
                                Ambassador May 22, 1936,<note n="50" xml:id="d485fn50">Department of
                                    State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, June 13, 1936, p.
                                    582.</note> states that this Government is fully disposed to
                                discuss, through diplomatic channels, any proposals which the
                                Italian Government may desire to put forward in regard to the
                                payment of its indebtedness to the United States, and that such
                                proposals would receive careful consideration with a view to
                                eventual submission to the American Congress.</p>
                            <pb facs="0676" n="596" xml:id="pg_596"/>
                            <p>The Department would be glad to discuss informally any proposals that
                                the Italian Government may initiate through diplomatic channels at
                                Washington.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>